00:24:55.536 --> 00:24:56.636 A:middle
things we're talking about

00:24:56.756 --> 00:24:57.076 A:middle
today.

00:24:57.676 --> 00:25:00.706 A:middle
Now, this is a page in "Learn to

00:25:00.706 --> 00:25:01.966 A:middle
Code" that's expanded out to

00:25:01.966 --> 00:25:03.416 A:middle
show off all the different areas

00:25:03.416 --> 00:25:04.376 A:middle
that you have to worry about

00:25:04.376 --> 00:25:05.366 A:middle
when you localize.

00:25:06.446 --> 00:25:07.766 A:middle
So on the right you'll see the

00:25:07.766 --> 00:25:09.126 A:middle
live view, but you can have

00:25:09.126 --> 00:25:10.556 A:middle
strings presented to the user.

00:25:10.916 --> 00:25:12.646 A:middle
In this case the audio controls.

00:25:14.236 --> 00:25:15.956 A:middle
There's also prose providing

00:25:15.956 --> 00:25:17.156 A:middle
instructional text.

00:25:18.336 --> 00:25:21.706 A:middle
The editable code area which is

00:25:21.706 --> 00:25:22.916 A:middle
a text that is displayed to the

00:25:22.916 --> 00:25:24.666 A:middle
user before they begin writing

00:25:24.666 --> 00:25:27.696 A:middle
codes to provide a prompt.

00:25:27.826 --> 00:25:28.936 A:middle
Each page can have a title.

00:25:30.456 --> 00:25:31.916 A:middle
Then also different glossary

00:25:31.916 --> 00:25:33.726 A:middle
terms which have definitions for

00:25:33.726 --> 00:25:34.866 A:middle
the learner to learn more about

00:25:34.866 --> 00:25:35.906 A:middle
if they forgot a term.

00:25:36.476 --> 00:25:39.266 A:middle
And a page can have one or more

00:25:39.266 --> 00:25:40.816 A:middle
hints if you want to provide

00:25:40.816 --> 00:25:42.316 A:middle
help for your learner as they're

00:25:42.316 --> 00:25:44.336 A:middle
going through and learning a

00:25:46.536 --> 00:25:46.766 A:middle
concept.

00:25:46.846 --> 00:25:48.376 A:middle
So these are all the different

00:25:48.376 --> 00:25:49.876 A:middle
parts we'll talk about showing

00:25:49.876 --> 00:25:51.416 A:middle
how to localize and what you

00:25:51.416 --> 00:25:53.246 A:middle
need to do for each of them.

00:25:53.246 --> 00:25:54.256 A:middle
And these come in a few

00:25:54.256 --> 00:25:56.126 A:middle
different types of files for

00:25:56.126 --> 00:25:56.956 A:middle
Playgrounds.

00:25:57.296 --> 00:25:58.376 A:middle
You might use a string in a

00:25:58.376 --> 00:26:00.276 A:middle
stringsdict file as well as an

00:26:00.276 --> 00:26:01.326 A:middle
xml plist.

00:26:01.846 --> 00:26:03.846 A:middle
And the cut scenes are written

00:26:03.846 --> 00:26:04.606 A:middle
in html.

00:26:05.236 --> 00:26:06.656 A:middle
And you may also have localized

00:26:06.656 --> 00:26:07.226 A:middle
assets.

00:26:07.496 --> 00:26:08.486 A:middle
So just do a change in each

00:26:08.486 --> 00:26:10.546 A:middle
image for each language to adapt

00:26:11.076 --> 00:26:11.146 A:middle
it.

00:26:12.436 --> 00:26:13.926 A:middle
Now one other detail before we

00:26:13.926 --> 00:26:15.606 A:middle
begin diving into the details is

00:26:15.606 --> 00:26:16.866 A:middle
understanding the overall

00:26:16.866 --> 00:26:18.806 A:middle
structure of a playground book.

00:26:19.336 --> 00:26:21.336 A:middle
So at a base level here, you see

00:26:21.336 --> 00:26:22.766 A:middle
you have a sources directory and

00:26:22.766 --> 00:26:24.226 A:middle
a private resources directory.

00:26:24.836 --> 00:26:26.166 A:middle
And the thing to note here is

00:26:26.166 --> 00:26:27.326 A:middle
that in the private resources

00:26:27.326 --> 00:26:29.216 A:middle
directory, you'll have an lproj

00:26:29.416 --> 00:26:30.156 A:middle
for each language you're

00:26:30.156 --> 00:26:30.666 A:middle
supporting.

00:26:31.216 --> 00:26:32.266 A:middle
In this example we're doing

00:26:32.266 --> 00:26:33.706 A:middle
English and Spanish, with

00:26:33.706 --> 00:26:35.106 A:middle
English being our development

00:26:35.106 --> 00:26:35.536 A:middle
language.

00:26:36.716 --> 00:26:39.086 A:middle
Then there is one or more

00:26:39.206 --> 00:26:41.016 A:middle
chapters in each book.

00:26:41.476 --> 00:26:43.986 A:middle
And each chapter has one or more

00:26:43.986 --> 00:26:44.466 A:middle
pages.

00:26:44.846 --> 00:26:46.096 A:middle
And this is an example in one of

00:26:46.096 --> 00:26:47.616 A:middle
the pages in a book.

00:26:48.116 --> 00:26:49.236 A:middle
And again, the thing to note

00:26:49.236 --> 00:26:50.556 A:middle
here is that the private

00:26:50.556 --> 00:26:52.156 A:middle
resource directory has those

00:26:52.156 --> 00:26:53.876 A:middle
same lproj's for each language

00:26:53.876 --> 00:26:54.536 A:middle
you are supporting.

00:26:55.646 --> 00:26:57.446 A:middle
So what does this look like for

00:26:57.446 --> 00:26:58.126 A:middle
each of the things?

00:26:58.306 --> 00:27:00.166 A:middle
Well, the strings that you have

00:27:00.166 --> 00:27:01.996 A:middle
in the live view, these you

00:27:01.996 --> 00:27:03.616 A:middle
should use in this localized

00:27:03.616 --> 00:27:05.426 A:middle
string for any time you are

00:27:05.836 --> 00:27:06.846 A:middle
using a string that will be

00:27:06.846 --> 00:27:07.946 A:middle
presented to the user.

00:27:08.736 --> 00:27:10.836 A:middle
And a thing to note here is that

00:27:10.836 --> 00:27:12.316 A:middle
it's not just things that

00:27:12.316 --> 00:27:13.376 A:middle
visually appear in the Live

00:27:13.376 --> 00:27:15.036 A:middle
View, but this also is important

00:27:15.036 --> 00:27:16.016 A:middle
for accessibility.

00:27:16.506 --> 00:27:18.046 A:middle
All of your accessibility labels

00:27:18.046 --> 00:27:20.336 A:middle
should use NSLocalizedString, so

00:27:20.336 --> 00:27:21.806 A:middle
that when someone is using the

00:27:21.806 --> 00:27:23.026 A:middle
accessibility features in

00:27:23.026 --> 00:27:24.796 A:middle
another language, they can get

00:27:24.796 --> 00:27:26.466 A:middle
the proper voiceover in their

00:27:26.466 --> 00:27:27.456 A:middle
language and have a great

00:27:27.456 --> 00:27:28.646 A:middle
experience with your content.

00:27:29.246 --> 00:27:32.196 A:middle
Now once you use

00:27:32.196 --> 00:27:33.856 A:middle
NSLocalizedString you would

00:27:33.856 --> 00:27:35.326 A:middle
extract this into the strings

00:27:35.326 --> 00:27:36.766 A:middle
file with a tool we made called

00:27:36.766 --> 00:27:37.376 A:middle
genstrings.

00:27:37.376 --> 00:27:39.576 A:middle
And there's more information on

00:27:39.576 --> 00:27:41.016 A:middle
the developers site of how to

00:27:41.016 --> 00:27:42.986 A:middle
use this tool and extract it.

00:27:44.806 --> 00:27:46.516 A:middle
And there was also a talk

00:27:46.856 --> 00:27:48.156 A:middle
earlier this week on localizing

00:27:48.156 --> 00:27:49.766 A:middle
with Xcode 9 that goes through a

00:27:49.766 --> 00:27:51.346 A:middle
lot of general best practices

00:27:51.346 --> 00:27:54.306 A:middle
with localizing in Xcode.

00:27:54.706 --> 00:27:56.396 A:middle
Now one key thing to note that

00:27:56.396 --> 00:27:57.626 A:middle
you might do in your playground

00:27:58.066 --> 00:28:00.386 A:middle
is using an image with text.

00:28:00.566 --> 00:28:02.526 A:middle
And it's really critical here to

00:28:02.526 --> 00:28:04.256 A:middle
not hardcode the text into the

00:28:04.256 --> 00:28:06.126 A:middle
image, as this will make it very

00:28:06.126 --> 00:28:07.846 A:middle
difficult to localize, requiring

00:28:07.846 --> 00:28:09.636 A:middle
you to remake the image for each

00:28:09.636 --> 00:28:10.176 A:middle
language.

00:28:10.746 --> 00:28:12.406 A:middle
Instead, you can layer the text

00:28:12.406 --> 00:28:14.566 A:middle
on top of it to enable the

00:28:14.566 --> 00:28:16.146 A:middle
translator just to translate the

00:28:16.146 --> 00:28:17.956 A:middle
strings and take advantage of

00:28:17.956 --> 00:28:19.716 A:middle
all of iOS's layout capabilities

00:28:19.746 --> 00:28:21.716 A:middle
to have a great experience for

00:28:23.956 --> 00:28:24.366 A:middle
the learner.

00:28:24.366 --> 00:28:26.396 A:middle
Now once you have these files,

00:28:26.396 --> 00:28:27.366 A:middle
the string file will get

00:28:27.366 --> 00:28:29.256 A:middle
extracted into the base level

00:28:29.506 --> 00:28:30.906 A:middle
private resources folder in the

00:28:30.906 --> 00:28:31.336 A:middle
project.

00:28:32.446 --> 00:28:33.986 A:middle
And optionally for using a

00:28:33.986 --> 00:28:35.846 A:middle
stringsdict file to dynamically

00:28:35.846 --> 00:28:37.226 A:middle
reference a number, such as how

00:28:37.226 --> 00:28:38.336 A:middle
many lines of code the learner

00:28:38.336 --> 00:28:39.766 A:middle
has written, you would create a

00:28:39.766 --> 00:28:41.106 A:middle
stringsdict file for that as

00:28:41.106 --> 00:28:42.236 A:middle
well in the same directory.

00:28:43.466 --> 00:28:47.206 A:middle
So the next piece is the prose.

00:28:48.066 --> 00:28:50.206 A:middle
And this is rendered in markups

00:28:50.466 --> 00:28:51.536 A:middle
to the form of markdown.

00:28:52.536 --> 00:28:53.716 A:middle
And this enables page level

00:28:53.716 --> 00:28:54.306 A:middle
formatting.

00:28:54.566 --> 00:28:56.766 A:middle
You can do bolding, italics, you

00:28:56.766 --> 00:28:58.946 A:middle
can create glossary terms or

00:28:58.946 --> 00:29:00.116 A:middle
link to another page in the

00:29:00.116 --> 00:29:00.416 A:middle
book.

00:29:01.086 --> 00:29:03.106 A:middle
And because of this, you have

00:29:03.106 --> 00:29:04.406 A:middle
this different markup format

00:29:04.466 --> 00:29:05.506 A:middle
that your translators will need

00:29:05.506 --> 00:29:07.046 A:middle
to be aware of to take advantage

00:29:07.046 --> 00:29:07.236 A:middle
of.

00:29:07.766 --> 00:29:09.826 A:middle
So as Aaltan said, you want to

00:29:09.826 --> 00:29:11.046 A:middle
tell all of your translators to

00:29:11.046 --> 00:29:13.606 A:middle
have editorial freedom to adjust

00:29:13.606 --> 00:29:15.316 A:middle
maybe the bolding or the style

00:29:15.426 --> 00:29:16.326 A:middle
per language.

00:29:16.756 --> 00:29:17.576 A:middle
And so they really need to

00:29:17.576 --> 00:29:19.206 A:middle
understand the format in order

00:29:19.206 --> 00:29:20.196 A:middle
to be able to do so.

00:29:21.196 --> 00:29:22.856 A:middle
And it's also important that

00:29:22.856 --> 00:29:24.406 A:middle
they be aware of what terms

00:29:24.406 --> 00:29:26.186 A:middle
cannot be translated that are

00:29:26.186 --> 00:29:28.066 A:middle
actually part of the format so

00:29:28.066 --> 00:29:29.146 A:middle
that they don't accidentally

00:29:29.146 --> 00:29:30.496 A:middle
introduce errors in the code

00:29:30.766 --> 00:29:31.896 A:middle
when they go to localize it.

00:29:32.996 --> 00:29:35.816 A:middle
now how do you make your prose

00:29:35.816 --> 00:29:36.446 A:middle
localizable?

00:29:36.876 --> 00:29:39.116 A:middle
Well, you start a prose block by

00:29:39.116 --> 00:29:40.416 A:middle
this little opening comment

00:29:40.416 --> 00:29:42.336 A:middle
here, and then you add a

00:29:42.336 --> 00:29:43.436 A:middle
localized key.

00:29:43.636 --> 00:29:44.566 A:middle
In this case we're calling it

00:29:44.566 --> 00:29:46.096 A:middle
firstproseblock as a name for

00:29:46.096 --> 00:29:46.556 A:middle
this key.

00:29:46.916 --> 00:29:48.056 A:middle
This will enable it to be

00:29:48.056 --> 00:29:48.666 A:middle
localized.

00:29:50.056 --> 00:29:51.686 A:middle
And then in your lproj you'll

00:29:51.686 --> 00:29:53.656 A:middle
create a prose.strings file and

00:29:53.856 --> 00:29:56.376 A:middle
put that same key there and then

00:29:56.646 --> 00:29:57.996 A:middle
set the value for whatever the

00:29:57.996 --> 00:29:58.826 A:middle
markup that should be

00:29:58.826 --> 00:29:59.896 A:middle
substituted in for that

00:29:59.896 --> 00:30:00.596 A:middle
language.

00:30:01.116 --> 00:30:05.856 A:middle
And the contents.swift resides

00:30:05.856 --> 00:30:07.016 A:middle
at the base directory for each

00:30:07.016 --> 00:30:07.566 A:middle
page.

00:30:08.026 --> 00:30:10.076 A:middle
But the prose.strings file will

00:30:10.076 --> 00:30:12.056 A:middle
be in the private resources for

00:30:12.056 --> 00:30:12.666 A:middle
each language that you're

00:30:12.666 --> 00:30:12.956 A:middle
supporting.

00:30:18.866 --> 00:30:20.626 A:middle
Next is the editable text field

00:30:20.626 --> 00:30:21.406 A:middle
placeholders.

00:30:21.946 --> 00:30:24.046 A:middle
So these are another strings

00:30:24.046 --> 00:30:24.456 A:middle
file.

00:30:24.456 --> 00:30:25.846 A:middle
And you see here the tap to

00:30:25.846 --> 00:30:26.506 A:middle
tenter code.

00:30:27.476 --> 00:30:28.726 A:middle
So how this is defined in the

00:30:28.726 --> 00:30:30.376 A:middle
initial language is just in a

00:30:30.376 --> 00:30:31.176 A:middle
code comment.

00:30:31.666 --> 00:30:32.576 A:middle
Where you see in the

00:30:32.576 --> 00:30:34.166 A:middle
contents.swift tap to enter

00:30:34.166 --> 00:30:34.516 A:middle
code.

00:30:35.086 --> 00:30:38.086 A:middle
And for this to be localizable,

00:30:38.376 --> 00:30:39.286 A:middle
you'll create an editable

00:30:39.286 --> 00:30:41.936 A:middle
field.strings file using the key

00:30:42.216 --> 00:30:43.666 A:middle
being the initial phrase you

00:30:43.666 --> 00:30:45.526 A:middle
created in your contents.swift.

00:30:46.016 --> 00:30:48.066 A:middle
So again, tap to enter code, but

00:30:48.066 --> 00:30:49.326 A:middle
you put in the appropriate

00:30:49.326 --> 00:30:50.606 A:middle
translation for each other

00:30:50.606 --> 00:30:51.636 A:middle
language you're supporting.

00:30:52.106 --> 00:30:56.036 A:middle
And this is done at the base

00:30:56.036 --> 00:30:57.766 A:middle
directory of the Playground book

00:30:57.766 --> 00:30:59.306 A:middle
in the private resources for the

00:30:59.306 --> 00:31:00.806 A:middle
associated languages.

00:31:01.306 --> 00:31:05.266 A:middle
Next up is a page and chapter

00:31:05.266 --> 00:31:05.766 A:middle
titles.

00:31:06.806 --> 00:31:09.046 A:middle
And so here there is a manifest

00:31:09.046 --> 00:31:10.526 A:middle
plist.strings file that you'll

00:31:10.526 --> 00:31:12.166 A:middle
need to create for each page or

00:31:12.166 --> 00:31:14.866 A:middle
chapter, and in this the app is

00:31:14.866 --> 00:31:16.846 A:middle
looking for the key name to

00:31:16.846 --> 00:31:18.626 A:middle
substitute in the new name for

00:31:18.626 --> 00:31:20.506 A:middle
the localized title for your

00:31:20.506 --> 00:31:20.836 A:middle
book.

00:31:21.266 --> 00:31:26.246 A:middle
And this is put in, again, the

00:31:26.246 --> 00:31:28.176 A:middle
private resources for that

00:31:28.176 --> 00:31:29.866 A:middle
particular page for each

00:31:29.866 --> 00:31:30.796 A:middle
language project.

00:31:32.516 --> 00:31:35.016 A:middle
So next up is the glossary.

00:31:35.016 --> 00:31:36.696 A:middle
And this is changing the format

00:31:36.696 --> 00:31:37.976 A:middle
as it's using XML.

00:31:38.366 --> 00:31:39.666 A:middle
And you'll need to make a copy

00:31:39.666 --> 00:31:40.596 A:middle
for this for each language

00:31:40.596 --> 00:31:41.276 A:middle
you're supporting.

00:31:41.906 --> 00:31:43.566 A:middle
But here is an example of the

00:31:43.566 --> 00:31:44.606 A:middle
English glossary.

00:31:45.456 --> 00:31:46.476 A:middle
And we're looking at what the

00:31:46.476 --> 00:31:48.666 A:middle
command definition is in

00:31:48.666 --> 00:31:49.156 A:middle
English.

00:31:50.026 --> 00:31:52.256 A:middle
So one thing to note here is

00:31:52.256 --> 00:31:54.166 A:middle
that the top level key command

00:31:54.636 --> 00:31:56.246 A:middle
is going to be the same across

00:31:56.246 --> 00:31:57.136 A:middle
every language.

00:31:57.626 --> 00:31:58.546 A:middle
This will be how the [applause]

00:31:58.546 --> 00:32:00.166 A:middle
looks up the glossary definition

00:32:00.166 --> 00:32:01.646 A:middle
and will not change.

00:32:02.746 --> 00:32:04.816 A:middle
Similarly, the page reference

00:32:05.076 --> 00:32:07.046 A:middle
should use a -- be by file

00:32:07.046 --> 00:32:08.776 A:middle
reference and not be page

00:32:08.776 --> 00:32:10.576 A:middle
referencing the title, which can

00:32:10.576 --> 00:32:11.416 A:middle
cause it to break in

00:32:11.416 --> 00:32:12.796 A:middle
localization if you were to

00:32:12.796 --> 00:32:13.576 A:middle
change the title.

00:32:14.116 --> 00:32:17.236 A:middle
And then there are several

00:32:17.236 --> 00:32:18.436 A:middle
different strings that you will

00:32:18.436 --> 00:32:19.926 A:middle
send off to your translator to

00:32:19.926 --> 00:32:21.656 A:middle
localize that you see here.

00:32:22.576 --> 00:32:24.216 A:middle
So if this is put into Spanish,

00:32:25.096 --> 00:32:26.696 A:middle
you then see the -- that overall

00:32:26.696 --> 00:32:28.016 A:middle
everything is the same, except

00:32:28.016 --> 00:32:29.666 A:middle
for those three strings get

00:32:29.666 --> 00:32:31.476 A:middle
localized and will be displayed

00:32:31.476 --> 00:32:33.426 A:middle
appropriately when the user runs

00:32:33.736 --> 00:32:35.346 A:middle
the app in Spanish.

00:32:35.866 --> 00:32:38.966 A:middle
And this glossary is stored at

00:32:38.966 --> 00:32:40.656 A:middle
the base-level private resources

00:32:40.946 --> 00:32:41.636 A:middle
in the project.

00:32:41.696 --> 00:32:43.506 A:middle
So you'd have one in your

00:32:43.506 --> 00:32:45.996 A:middle
English lproj, and then also a

00:32:45.996 --> 00:32:47.886 A:middle
copy that's been translated for

00:32:47.886 --> 00:32:48.766 A:middle
your Spanish project.

00:32:51.256 --> 00:32:54.006 A:middle
Hints follow a similar format as

00:32:54.006 --> 00:32:55.776 A:middle
the glossary in that they are

00:32:55.776 --> 00:32:56.966 A:middle
using XML as well.

00:32:57.296 --> 00:32:58.646 A:middle
But these are done on a per page

00:32:58.646 --> 00:32:58.956 A:middle
level.

00:32:59.486 --> 00:33:02.456 A:middle
And each page can have one or

00:33:02.456 --> 00:33:03.706 A:middle
more hints if desired.

00:33:04.386 --> 00:33:05.906 A:middle
And this is an example of what a

00:33:05.906 --> 00:33:06.906 A:middle
hint file looks like.

00:33:07.606 --> 00:33:09.136 A:middle
And in it are several different

00:33:09.136 --> 00:33:10.566 A:middle
strings that your translators

00:33:10.566 --> 00:33:11.526 A:middle
will need to translate.

00:33:12.566 --> 00:33:13.796 A:middle
And so to -- you would make a

00:33:13.796 --> 00:33:16.076 A:middle
copy of this file and have them

00:33:16.076 --> 00:33:18.096 A:middle
localize these strings, and then

00:33:18.096 --> 00:33:19.066 A:middle
you would get this output.

00:33:19.626 --> 00:33:22.746 A:middle
And this new hintplist, this

00:33:22.746 --> 00:33:24.056 A:middle
goes in the private resources

00:33:24.056 --> 00:33:25.836 A:middle
directory for that page, as they

00:33:25.836 --> 00:33:26.946 A:middle
only apply to that particular

00:33:26.946 --> 00:33:27.456 A:middle
page.

00:33:27.926 --> 00:33:29.136 A:middle
And you'd have both the English

00:33:29.136 --> 00:33:31.436 A:middle
version and the Spanish version.

00:33:31.996 --> 00:33:36.206 A:middle
And so last up are the animated

00:33:36.206 --> 00:33:38.026 A:middle
cut scenes, which are html

00:33:38.026 --> 00:33:38.606 A:middle
files.

00:33:39.176 --> 00:33:40.996 A:middle
And these, your translators will

00:33:40.996 --> 00:33:42.226 A:middle
need to make a copy for each

00:33:42.226 --> 00:33:43.786 A:middle
language and appropriately

00:33:43.786 --> 00:33:45.796 A:middle
localize the strings, as well as

00:33:45.796 --> 00:33:47.236 A:middle
potentially change any of the

00:33:47.236 --> 00:33:50.076 A:middle
concepts or images as needed per

00:33:50.076 --> 00:33:50.906 A:middle
each language.

00:33:51.416 --> 00:33:54.426 A:middle
And when they do this, you will

00:33:54.426 --> 00:33:56.296 A:middle
need to put it in the cut scene

00:33:56.296 --> 00:33:57.726 A:middle
pages private resources

00:33:57.726 --> 00:33:58.216 A:middle
directory.

00:33:58.836 --> 00:34:00.116 A:middle
So here we see the English

00:34:00.116 --> 00:34:01.396 A:middle
version is called

00:34:01.396 --> 00:34:03.476 A:middle
conditionalcode.html.

00:34:03.476 --> 00:34:05.776 A:middle
And the initial html file for

00:34:05.776 --> 00:34:07.206 A:middle
each other language needs to

00:34:07.206 --> 00:34:08.826 A:middle
follow that exact same name.

00:34:09.286 --> 00:34:10.836 A:middle
So for Spanish, even though

00:34:10.836 --> 00:34:11.796 A:middle
it'll have all the localized

00:34:11.796 --> 00:34:13.506 A:middle
terms, the file name should be

00:34:13.536 --> 00:34:15.026 A:middle
conditionalcode.html.

00:34:15.626 --> 00:34:20.036 A:middle
So in summary today, we covered

00:34:20.036 --> 00:34:21.456 A:middle
a lot about localization.

00:34:21.856 --> 00:34:23.026 A:middle
And one thing that's really key

00:34:23.026 --> 00:34:25.166 A:middle
to remember is to define who

00:34:25.166 --> 00:34:26.886 A:middle
your audience is, and be sure to

00:34:26.886 --> 00:34:28.566 A:middle
understand them when you're

00:34:28.566 --> 00:34:29.706 A:middle
going into each different

00:34:29.706 --> 00:34:31.046 A:middle
language and trying to adapt the

00:34:31.046 --> 00:34:31.646 A:middle
content.

00:34:32.996 --> 00:34:34.856 A:middle
Localization is really nuance

00:34:34.856 --> 00:34:35.596 A:middle
and complex.

00:34:35.906 --> 00:34:37.406 A:middle
It requires a lot of research

00:34:37.406 --> 00:34:39.266 A:middle
and testing with actual users,

00:34:39.536 --> 00:34:40.636 A:middle
and understanding what are the

00:34:40.636 --> 00:34:42.636 A:middle
standards for each country or

00:34:42.636 --> 00:34:44.076 A:middle
language or region that you want

00:34:44.076 --> 00:34:44.676 A:middle
to go into.

00:34:45.226 --> 00:34:48.606 A:middle
And one thing to keep in mind of

00:34:48.606 --> 00:34:51.096 A:middle
all this is that localization is

00:34:51.176 --> 00:34:52.166 A:middle
really part of the design

00:34:52.166 --> 00:34:53.056 A:middle
process.

00:34:53.216 --> 00:34:54.516 A:middle
And so you should be thinking

00:34:54.516 --> 00:34:56.426 A:middle
about localization up front if

00:34:56.426 --> 00:34:57.386 A:middle
you want to have an amazing

00:34:57.386 --> 00:34:58.726 A:middle
experience for your users.

00:34:59.166 --> 00:35:01.026 A:middle
And I encourage you all to do

00:35:01.026 --> 00:35:02.596 A:middle
so, and make amazing content

00:35:02.876 --> 00:35:03.876 A:middle
that everyone in the world can

00:35:03.876 --> 00:35:04.626 A:middle
experience.

